@startuml
!include ../style.puml

title distrib-txn-db Workshop Roadmap

skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 15
}

' [step1 {"name":"Module 01 and 02 foundations"}]
rectangle "01-hybrid-clock\nHybridClock + HybridTimestamp" as m1
rectangle "02-versioned-kv\nMVCC keys, versions, scans" as m2

m1 -right-> m2 : timestamps index versions
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Module 03 adds distributed routing"}]
rectangle "03-distrib-versioned-kv\nhash(key) routing\npropagate HLC on RPC" as m3

m2 -right-> m3 : route reads and writes
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Module 04 adds distributed transactions"}]
rectangle "04-distrib-txn-kv\nbegin txn\nintents\nsnapshot reads\ncommit + resolve" as m4

m3 -right-> m4 : build SI on top of MVCC
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"Module 05 adds clock uncertainty handling"}]
rectangle "05-clock-uncertainty-and-read-restart\nuncertainty window\nread restart fix" as m5

m4 -right-> m5 : fix skewed snapshot reads
' [/step4]

' [step5 {"name":"Module 06 adds serializable validation"}]
rectangle "06-serializable-txn\nread provisional records\nblock write skew" as m6

m5 -right-> m6 : go beyond snapshot isolation

note bottom
The workshop starts with time, then uses that time in MVCC,
then turns it into distributed transactions, then fixes
clock uncertainty, and finally blocks write skew.
end note
' [/step5]

@enduml
